    <name>
      <text>Finding Focus, Vertices, and Asymptotes of a Hyperbola</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<br> Find the foci, vertices, and asymptotes of hyperbola \( {@expr@} \).

<br> a) Focus 
<br>\( F_{1}=\)  [[input:ans1]]  \( F_{2}=\)  [[input:ans2]]   <br>\(\qquad\) [[validation:ans1]] [[validation:ans2]]  [[feedback:prtA]]

<br> b) Vertices
<br> \( A_{1}=\)  [[input:ans3]]  \( A_{2}=\)  [[input:ans4]]   <br>\(\qquad\)[[validation:ans3]] [[validation:ans4]]  [[feedback:prtB]]

<br> c) Asymptotes: 
<br> \( l_{1}=\)  [[input:ans5]] \( l_{2}=\)  [[input:ans6]]  
<br> \(\qquad\) [[validation:ans5]] [[validation:ans6]]  [[feedback:prtC]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<br><b>Worked solution</b>
<br><b>Recall:</b> Summary of Standard Equations of Hyperbola
<br> <table border="1" width="60%">
        <tr>
            <td width="40%">Equation</td>
            <td>Centre</td>
            <td>Vertices</td>
            <td width="30%">Foci</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>\(\displaystyle \frac{{(x-h)^2}}{{a^2}} - \frac{{(y-k)^2}}{{b^2}} = 1\)</td>
            <td>\((h, k)\)</td>
            <td>\((h \pm a, k)\)</td>
            <td>\((h \pm \sqrt{{a^2 + b^2}}, k)\)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>\(\displaystyle \frac{{(y-k)^2}}{{a^2}} - \frac{{(x-h)^2}}{{b^2}} = 1\)</td>
            <td>\((h, k)\)</td>
            <td>\((h, k \pm a)\)</td>
            <td>\((h, k \pm \sqrt{{a^2 + b^2}})\)</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

<br>We need to write  \({@expr@} \) in standard form \(\displaystyle \implies  \frac{(x-h)^2}{a^2}- \frac{(y-k)^2}{b^2}=1.\)
<br> Rearrange the eqn as follows;
<br>{@hyper2_2@}
<br>
<br> Use completing square method to factories the equation.
<br>\(\displaystyle {@lhs(hyper2_1)@}=  {@rhs(hyper2_2)@}- {@val_b^2@}({@h^2@}) + {@val_a^2@}({@k^2@}) \)
<br>
<br>{@hyper2@}
<br>
<br>\(\displaystyle{@hyper1@}\)
<br>
<br> Note: \(\displaystyle  h= {@h@},   k= {@k@},   a= {@val_a@},   b = {@val_b@}\) and \(c =\sqrt(a^2+b^2)= {@c@}\)

<br>
<br>From here,
<br>
<br> a) Focus : \( (h \pm c, k) \implies  ({@focus1_x@}, {@focus1_y@})\) and   \(({@focus2_x@}, {@focus2_y@}) \)
<br>
<br> b) Vertices: \( (h \pm a, k) \implies  ({@ver1_x@}, {@ver1_y@})\) and   \( ({@ver2_x@}, {@ver2_y@}) \)
<br>
<br> c) Asymptotes: \( y-k=\pm {@(b/a)@} \cdot (x-h) \);
<br>
<br> Which simplifies to;
<br> \( \displaystyle l_{1}: {@l1@} \Leftrightarrow {@l1_expd@} \)
<br> \(\displaystyle  l_{2}: {@l2@} \Leftrightarrow {@l2_expd@} \)]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
